<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-21T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="692" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">752.822/3: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-21T18:00:00-04:00">August
                                        21, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>32. Your 47, August 18, 9 p.m. We earnestly hope that the Liberian
                                Government will take no action on the Spanish proposals pending our
                                further study of the matter, the results of which will be
                                communicated to you shortly.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>